This "new base" configuration is the Keck LGS AO as of June 2026, modified from the description below. I've tried to keep both configurations
and label them accordingly as new and old (or pre & post-KAPA)
- The LGS WFS has been updated to the measured parameters for the OCAM2K camera installed with KAPA in ~Nov 2024
- The LGS WFS runs at 500Hz
- KAPA lets you run with a 4 LGS constellation on the OCAM2K at the cost of 1/4th or 1/8th the laser power per LGS
- STRAP, the tip-tilt WFS runs at 1kHz
- TRICK is a new near-IR tip-tilt WFS which I have configured to run in 4x4 mode at 1kHz 
- TRICK operates either at H or K band, whichever is complementary to the band the science camera is using (evl.wvl in H or K band should be the opposite)
- good_powfs_common.conf & good_powfs_none.conf have been added locally. MAOS will check for files in the maos config directory before checking locally, so 
  these need to be unique names (hence the "good" prefix instead of just including powfs_none.conf)
- The tip-tilt WFS signal levels are set based on a NEA of 1.93 on STRAP for 472Hz from old base. This corresponds with an NGS star which is 8.09 mag
  NOT the R=10 mag shown below. See find_keck_nea_photons_params.ipynb in this folder which goes through the fit using paarti.utils.maos_utils.keck_nea_photons.
  We assume that a star whichi s 8.09 mag in the R band seen by STRAP with a center of 720nm is also seen at 8.09 mag in the H and K band by TRICK-H & -K

OLD BASE:
This "base" configuration is the Keck LGS AO <2023 hardware with the following observing situation:

- Optical STRAP for tip-tilt sensing
- NGS (TT and LBWFS) star is engineering star:  R=10 mag, on-axis
- Zenith angle is 30 deg.
- Running AO system at 472 Hz (high-order LGSWFS and TT)
- 130 nm of Keck primary segment piston error (via ncpa surf parameter)
- extra tip-tilt blur from wind-shake and jitter (via ncpa temporal PSD parameter)


